# Cline Development Rules

## Module Structure
- The real Go module for the app is ./clicker
- Always run Go build/test commands from ./clicker
- Never run go test ./clicker/runner from repository root

## Command Execution
- Never use && because this is Windows PowerShell
- Use separate commands or semicolon ; for PowerShell
- If a command fails twice, stop and diagnose. Do not repeat it

## Development Practices
- Do not edit go.mod or create go.work unless explicitly requested
- Do not run go mod tidy unless explicitly requested
- Do not modify production code during analysis tasks
- Preserve existing detection/OCR/autopot logic unless explicitly requested
- Keep changes minimal and localized
- Before large refactors, first produce a plan and wait for approval